Hey this is Casey.

Since Matt has not updated in forever I decided to copy my friend Niki and update it for him. I also changed the theme of his journal. I think he'll like it. Don't worry I am doing this with his permission. He's currently engrossed in Zelda: Twilight Princess. That's all folks.
Lol. Hello.  This is my update.  All is well.  Later.

Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays everyone.  Just thought I would stop by and say hello.  I've been working and hanging out with Casey a lot lately.  Its nice.  Well I gotta get ready for work. Maybe I will update later.
-Matt-

Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In October I donated bone marrow to in a life-saving procedure (300 points). Last Thursday I ruled Asscrackistan as a kind and benevolent dictator (700 points). In November I put money in 's expired parking meter (14 points). In June I pushed in the mud (-17 points). In March I helped across the street (6 points).

Overall, I've been nice (1003 points). For Christmas I deserve a red Radio-Flyer wagon!

Sincerely,
thegrasso445

So yeah, I don't write all that often.  And ya know I just had the urge to come and write something in here.  So ya know, writing.  Its my day off.  And oh boy am I glad about that.  Days off rock.  I don't have to sit in front of that computer all day.  I am getting a hair cut, and I get to see Casey!!!!!  I like seeing Casey.  Its very nice. I am not spending the night but thats okay.  Just knowing I get to spend time with her is nice.  Well I guess thats all I really have to write.  Laters all.

So I have been told I do not update enough.  So here goes.  An update.  *GASP* Haha.  Anyhoo, I have a life now.  I am working 40 hours a week and then coming home and talkign to Casey.  On weekends I hang out with her.  Exciting I know.  But to me it is the best times in the world.  Today I get to hang out with Will.  Which is always nice.  Cause you know we never really see eachother anymore.  This weekend Casey and I are going to Hornell to visit Justin and Mary.  It will be fun.  So again you get a short update from me.  I know, I know.  But thats all I have to say for now.  Later.

I don't remember what I said last time I wrote in here. Haha. Last weekend was fun.  I spent it with Casey.  She is awesome.  I just thought I would say that again.  I went up Friday night, and we went to wegmans and got some stuff.  And then we went back to her dorm and watched movies it was fun.  Saturday morning we had breakfest and played some games on the computer.  Then we went to fright fest.  Fright fest was fun.  Yay Darien Lake.  I finally got to ride the superman.  It was a fun ride.  The preadator was also open.  But it kinda hurt.  I didn't remember that part.  Stupid getting fat.  Oh well.  The haunted house was a mixture of funny and scary.  I did jump once or twice.  We also went on the Viper.  It rained a little while we were waiting to go on the superman.  So after we did that we went to the arcade.  With our tickets combined we got Casey a cute little turtle.  It was fun. We went home after we had dinner cause it was freaking cold.  Sunday we went to the giant Wegmans, and Giant Barns and Nobles of doom.  The book store was fun.  Wegmans was crazy.   I also got to see Casey practice for the musical.  It was fun.  But I had to come home Monday.  Stupid home.  Well time for work.  Laters.

Casey is the best.  I got to spend most of the weekend with her.  Friday we spent pretty much the whole day together.  Casey was so sweet when I got to her house.  She made me a turkey sandwhich and gave me a pickle with it.  YUM!!!  After that we went to the mall.  I bought more stuff than I probably should have. FYE didn't have the full metal alchemist dvd she wanted, and neither did Waldens.  Stupid mall stores.  So we ended up going to Borders.  They had the dvd's and the Full Metal Alchemist dvd she wanted.  It was fun.  After that we went to Friendly's.  I had a honey barbacue chicken strip basket, and Casey had quesidillos.  We shared my ice cream afterwards.  Then we went and saw Corpse Bride.  It was good.  Saturday I got a suprise, Casey showed up at like 3:30.  They did not need her at work till 7.  So we hung out and then she went to work.  Afterwards she came back and we watched Inuyasha and Full Metal Alchemist.  She spent the nice.  It was nice.  Today we had breakfast and then went and exchanged her costume, and got some fun stuff.  She got wings and a wig.  I got shot glasses and a electric blue wig.  So I am going to be a ghostbuster with blue hair.  :P  So after that I was pretty much a lazy kid.  Lazy is fun.  Well Thats all for now I guess.  Casey is the best.  I am a very lucky boy to have her.  And it is awesome getting to sleep next to her.  Even though I apparently hiss while I sleep.  Thats kinda weird.  Oh well.  I get to see her again on Tuesday.  Woo Hoo.  Nintendo Fusion Tour Wenesday.  Laters all.

Your Seduction Style: Sweet Talker
Your seduction technique can be summed up with "charm" You know that if you have the chance to talk to someone... Well, you won't be talking for long! ;-) You're great at telling potential lovers what they want to hear. Partially, because you're a great reflective listener and good at complementing. The other part of your formula? Focusing your conversation completely on the other person. Your "sweet talking" ways have taken you far in romance - and in life. You can finess your way through any difficult situation, with a smile on your face. Speeding tickets, job interviews... bring it on! You truly live a *charmed life*
What Kind of Seducer Are You?
Meatball Pizza
Unusual and uncompromising. You're usually the first to discover a new trend. You appreciate a good meal and good company. You're an interesting blend of traditional and modern.
What's Your Pizza Personality?
You Are 80% Boyish and 20% Girlish
You have a tough exterior - and usually a tough interior to match it. You're no nonsense, logical, and very assertive. Sometimes you can't understand women at all, even if you're a woman yourself. You see things rationally, and don't like to let your emotions get the best of you.
How Boyish or Girlish Are You?
Your Brain's Pattern
Your brain is always looking for the connections in life. You always amaze your friends by figuring out things first. You're also good at connecting people - and often play match maker. You see the world in fluid, flexible terms. Nothing is black or white.
What Pattern Is Your Brain?
How You Are In Love
You take a while to fall in love with someone. Trust takes time. You give and take equally in relationships. You tend to get very attached when you're with someone. You want to see your love all the time. You love your partner unconditionally and don't try to make them change. You stay in love for a long time, even if you aren't loved back. When you fall, you fall hard.
How Are You In Love?
Your Kissing Purity Score: 54% Pure
For you, kissing isn't a casual thing Lip to lip action makes your heart sing
Kissing Purity Test
You Are an Emo Rocker!
Expressive and deep, lyrics are really your thing. That doesn't mean you don't rock out... You just rock out with meaning. For you, rock is more about connecting than grandstanding.
What Kind of Rocker Are You?
Your Inner Child Is Surprised
You see many things through the eyes of a child. Meaning, you're rarely cynical or jaded. You cherish all of the details in life. Easily fascinated, you enjoy experiencing new things.
How Is Your Inner Child?

I'm bored, and its what I am listening too.  On October 15th I will be going to Darien Lake Six Flags for the first time in my life.  I have been to plain old Darien Lake, but never six flags.  ANd its been Six Flags since like 99.  Going to fright fest with Casey. October 5th Nintendo Fusion tour. WOO HOO.  And October 31st, I am devirginized... To the Rocky Horror Picture Show.  Haha.  I am going to be a Ghostbuster.  Yay.  Well I don't have much else to write right now.  Laters all.

I'm sleepy.  Early shifts are not fun.  No they are not.  Work was busy today.  Last night was awesome.  I went and visited Casey.  Always fun.  We watched tv, listened to music, wandered around campus, and ate. It was fun.  We watched Smallville.  YAY SMALLVILLE.  Haha.  New season starts the 29ths. Freaking awesome.  I've started my new position at work.  Its not to bad.  A lot of little things, but I am learning to deal with it.  Well thats all.
Apparently i look really bad today.  Cause everyone says i look bad. I hope I just need sleep, cause I don't wanna be sick.  Oh well off to other things.

Why can't I beat you?!?!?!?  Oh well, still get to help casey move tommorow.  That will be fun.  Started full time today.  That means yes, I have finally gotten a real job.  Its still in the diet office but 40 hours a week.  I can get benefits and all that good stuff.  I donno, I'm really happy lately.  But I'm also really tired today.  So I'm probably gonna go to bed early today.  Oh sometimes I wish I didn't live at home.  I donno all done.

I don't know.  I'm bored.  So I thought I would write in this.  I been having the most amazing week ever.  I got full time at the hospital, I got Casey.  *HUGE GRIN*  I really like Casey. She is awesome.  We went and saw Skeleton Key last night.  It was okay.  I think Four Brothers was much, much better.  Oh well I guess I don't have anything else to say right now.  Later.

This has been a really really really good week.  Casey is awesome and makes me really happy.  And I'm gonna miss her when she goes away to Fisher.  But I will be able to visit her every other weekend.  Cause I got the full time position.  Which rocks my socks off.  40 hours a week means better paychecks.  *GRINS*  I would go as far as to say this is the best week ever.  And things will only get better from here.  I finally feel like my life is right about where I want it to be.  I met Caseys family last night.  They are cool.  I got to talk to her grandparents the most.  They seem really nice.  Last night we watched Labyrinth and Big Fish.  It was fun.  But the pizza gave me heat burn.  :P  Caseys dog Misty let me use her as a foot rest.  It was unintentional but fun.  I donno.  Its just been a really good week.  I kinda don't wanna go to work tommorow but oh well. I've got to learn to keep myself busy now.  I'm sure once I start the 11 o'clock I will be able to keep busy.  The one shift I am not looking forward to learning is the 5:30.  UGH!!!  Oh well, I'll just have to learn to go to bed early.  Haha.  But I'm excited cause I'll get to visit Casey and not wonder what weekends I'm gonna be able too.  Oh, and Will, Ashley, Casey and I are all going to the Nintendo Fusion Tour.  Well thats all.  I'm outtie.

This has been like the best week ever.  Casey and I are dating now, and I couldn't be happier.  I'm giddy and excited but I am also tired. So I think I'm gonna crash now.  I'll write more later maybe.  Night all.
Today was great. Casey is awesome, and I had a blast.  From x-box to the movies.  Today was just fun.  But I'm tired so im gonna hit the hey.

We have a bee infestation in my house.  Unfortunatley I didn't know that.  So when what holding them in fell off the ceiling and bees started crawling out it scared the fucking hell out of me.  We killed a bunch of them and got some outside.  We got the hole super duck tape fortified now.  But holy shit thats scary.  The exterminator can not get here fast enough.

Burnout 3 is a really awesome game.  But it can be soooooooo frustrating.  I just spent the last hour trying to do one race.  GAHH.  Oh well.  I donno, not much has happened today.  I went to work.  Fell asleep on the couch after I got back.  Ate dinner.  Played some games.  And now I'm typing here.  Well I'm outta here.  Later.

Ohh sorry. I was typing along to the guitar chords. :P I know. I'm being a dork. Well I took a quiz. Cause ya know, I do that sorta thing from time to time. Haha, well anyway here it is.
Which Finding Nemo Character Are You?
brought to you by Quizilla Oh yeah I'm in the big six percenter group. Lol. Well I guess I'm gonna split. Mark the places in my book with photographs we never took.

Casey and I went to see four brothers.  Awesome movie.  Its funny, sad and actiony all at the same time.  After the movie we went to the mall and ate little tokyo.  YUM! After that we walked around the mall.  Casey got a shirt for her friends birthday tommorow at hot topics.  I picked up so comics at fye.  Then we decided to look around Waldens book.  We found a Nightmare before christmas manga.  Good times were had by all.  Then we rode the escaloter in kaufmans and made mall rats jokes.  Then I took her home and she forgot to grab the cds I burned for her.  I also forgot to remind her.  Oh well thats all.  Laters.

So I took a stupid quiz. And I found a mario icon. I know I'm a dork. I also have free time they don't mix sometimes. I've been reading gasp. Oh and the quiz will be at the end of all of this. So just be paitent. So I read Fahrenheit 451, not to be confused with Michael Moore's Fahrenheit 911. Ones a movie, hte others a book by Ray Bradbury. Who by the way is probably one of the greatest authors of all time. Anyhoo I read the book again, haven't really read it since high school. And its still great. Especally the flame thrower. *BIG GRIN* I'm not gonna ruin it incase you haven't read the book. I think they are making a movie out of it too. I will go see it. And now I am reading a book called The Dante Club. Its by a guy named Matthew Pearl and it is very cool. It is set in 1865 right before the english translation of Dante's devine comedy is released. Their is a serial killer copying the events Dante's poem on his victims. Except it hasn't been released yet. So the Dante Club, which is famuos authors of the time. Is called solve the murders. The authors are James Lowell, Oliver Wendell Holmes, and Henry Longfellow. Any way its cool. Then I'm gonna read the Halloween Tree, and A Graveyard for Lunatics. Both are by Bradbury, and both are awesome. Well anyways heres the quiz I took. :P

Except we have to wait a month to see what happens next.  And they coast money.  Funny how that works.  :P  I have been reading a lot of comics lately.  I wanna get the whole House of M series.  That stuff is frigging good.  I know.  DORK.  But hey I'm happy.  LOL.  And comics books are better than soap operas anyways.  You can read them like 15 times in a day if you really wanted too.  Haha.  But anyways I wanna know what happens.  I wanna know if they wind up killing Wanda or if she gets better.  This crap is intretesting.  And addicting as well.  Oh and you never see them make videogames outta soap operas.  That would be freaky.  It would have to be like some fighting game, but like with I donno, ripping eachothers clothes off and throwing mud at eachother.  Like they dont have games like that already.  LOL.  Well thats enough rambling out of me for now.  Well I don't know if thats true I'm just outta things to say.

Hung out with Alisha, bobby, casey and sarah.  It was fun.  When we finally decided what we were gonna do that is.  :P haha.  Any ways we ended up going to the go-kart place in Macedon. It was fun. Well I guess thats all I really gots to say right now.  Later.

and its 2005.  I'm tired and feeling not to great.  Nothing really seems to be going the way I want.  I just dont know.  I miss my old friends.  As crazy as that sounds.  My friends now are cool as hell.  But my old friends were the shit.  Take it back to square one.  Gotta get it back too, back up when I find you, start exceleration, take it back to square one. The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to those who are unbridled, untrammeled, and free.
In love, you feel the most alive when your lover is creative and never lets you feel bored.
You'd like to your lover to think you are loyal and faithful... that you'll never change.
You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please.
Your ideal relationship is comforting. You crave a relationship where you always feel warmth and love.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage pessimistically. You don't think happy marriages exist anymore.
In this moment, you think of love as something you thirst for. You'll do anything for love, but you won't fall for it easily.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?
The only thing that isn't really accurate is the marriage thing. I don't really think of it that way.
